{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"hadithNawawi","displayName":"40 Hadith (An-Nawawi)","type":"quotes","language":"English","edition":"An-Nawawi's 40 Hadith, Public Domain","primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Islamic","audienceTags":["hadith","devotional"],"sortPriority":25,"itemCount":42,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"browseOrder":"sequence","groupingLevels":["hadith"],"groupingLabels":["Hadith"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Hadith_Nawawi40.json","version":"1.0"},"data":[{"id":"hadith-nawawi-1","text":"Actions are judged by intentions, and every person will get the reward according to what he has intended. So whoever emigrated for Allah and His Messenger, his emigration will be for Allah and His Messenger; and whoever emigrated for worldly benefits or for a woman to marry, his emigration would be for what he emigrated for.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #1 — narrated by Umar ibn al-Khattab (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":0},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-2","text":"Islam is built upon five pillars: testifying that there is no god but Allah and that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah, performing the prayers, paying the zakat, making the pilgrimage to the House, and fasting in Ramadan.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #2 — narrated by Ibn Umar (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":1},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-3","text":"Islam is built on five: testimony that there is no god but Allah and Muhammad is His Messenger, establishing prayer, giving zakat, hajj to the House, and fasting Ramadan. Then he was asked: And what is Islam? He said: That you testify that there is no god but Allah and that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah, that you establish prayer, give zakat, fast Ramadan, and make pilgrimage to the House if you are able. He said: You have spoken correctly.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #3 — narrated by Umar ibn al-Khattab (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":2},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-4","text":"The creation of each one of you comes together in his mother's womb for forty days as a drop of fluid, then it is a clinging form for a similar period, then a lump of flesh for a similar period. Then Allah sends an angel who is ordered to write four things: his provision, his lifespan, his deeds, and whether he will be wretched or blessed. Then a soul is breathed into him. By the One besides Whom there is no god, one of you may do the deeds of the people of Paradise until there is only a cubit between him and it, and then what is written overtakes him, and he does the deeds of the people of the Fire and enters it. And one of you may do the deeds of the people of the Fire until there is only a cubit between him and it, and then what is written overtakes him and he does the deeds of the people of Paradise and enters it.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #4 — narrated by Abdullah ibn Masud (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"4"},"sequenceIndex":3},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-5","text":"Verily the lawful is clear and the forbidden is clear, and between the two are doubtful matters that many people do not know. Whoever is careful about the doubtful matters, he has protected his religion and his honor. Whoever falls into the doubtful matters falls into the forbidden, just as the shepherd who pastures around a sanctuary will soon pasture in it. Surely every king has a sanctuary, and surely Allah's sanctuary is His prohibitions. Surely in the body there is a lump of flesh which, if it is sound, the whole body is sound, and if it is corrupt, the whole body is corrupt. Surely it is the heart.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #5 — narrated by An-Numan ibn Bashir (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"5"},"sequenceIndex":4},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-6","text":"The forbidden is what Allah has forbidden in His Book. What is silent about is a pardon. Accept the pardon of Allah, for indeed Allah is not forgetful of anything.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #6 — narrated by Abu Thalabah al-Khushani (al-Daraqutni)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"6"},"sequenceIndex":5},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-7","text":"Religion is sincere advice. We said: To whom? He replied: To Allah, His Book, His Messenger, and to the leaders of the Muslims and their common folk.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #7 — narrated by Tamim al-Dari (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"7"},"sequenceIndex":6},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-8","text":"I have been commanded to fight people until they testify that there is no god but Allah and that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah, and until they establish prayer and pay zakat. If they do that, their blood and property are protected from me except by the rights of Islam, and their reckoning will be with Allah.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #8 — narrated by Ibn Umar (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"8"},"sequenceIndex":7},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-9","text":"What I have forbidden you, avoid. What I have commanded you, do as much of it as you can. Verily, the people before you were destroyed only because of their excessive questioning and their disagreement with their prophets.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #9 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"9"},"sequenceIndex":8},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-10","text":"Allah the Exalted is pure and accepts only that which is pure. Allah has commanded the believers what He commanded the Messengers, saying: O Messengers, eat of the pure things and act righteously. And He said: O you who believe, eat of the pure things We have provided for you. Then he mentioned a man who has traveled a long way, whose hair is disheveled and covered with dust. He raises his hands to the sky and says: O Lord, O Lord! However, his food is unlawful, his drink is unlawful, his clothing is unlawful, and he is nourished by the unlawful, so how can he be answered?","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #10 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"10"},"sequenceIndex":9},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-11","text":"Abandon what is doubtful to you and turn to what is not doubtful.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #11 — narrated by Al-Hasan ibn Ali (Tirmidhi & Nasai)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"11"},"sequenceIndex":10},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-12","text":"Part of the perfection of a person's Islam is that he leaves alone what does not concern him.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #12 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"12"},"sequenceIndex":11},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-13","text":"None of you truly believes until he loves for his brother what he loves for himself.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #13 — narrated by Anas ibn Malik (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"13"},"sequenceIndex":12},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-14","text":"The blood of a Muslim person is not lawful unless he is one of three: a soul for a soul, and the married adulterer, and the apostate who abandons the community.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #14 — narrated by Ibn Masud (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"14"},"sequenceIndex":13},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-15","text":"Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him say something good or remain silent. Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him honor his neighbor. Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him honor his guest.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #15 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"15"},"sequenceIndex":14},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-16","text":"Do not get angry.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #16 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Bukhari)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"16"},"sequenceIndex":15},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-17","text":"Verily, Allah has decreed that you be excellent in all things. So if you kill, kill well; and if you slaughter, slaughter well. Let each one of you sharpen his blade and let him spare suffering to the animal he slaughters.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #17 — narrated by Shaddad ibn Aws (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"17"},"sequenceIndex":16},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-18","text":"Fear Allah wherever you may be, follow up an evil deed with a good one which will wipe it out, and behave well towards people.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #18 — narrated by Abu Dharr al-Ghifari & Muadh ibn Jabal (Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"18"},"sequenceIndex":17},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-19","text":"Guard well what Allah has entrusted you with, and you will be a believer.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #19 — narrated by Ibn Abbas (Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"19"},"sequenceIndex":18},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-20","text":"Be modest before Allah as is His due. We said: O Prophet of Allah, praise be to Allah, we are modest. He said: That is not it. But true modesty before Allah is that you guard your head and what it contains, and your stomach and what it is filled with, and remember death and trials, and whoever desires the Hereafter abandons the adornments of this world. Whoever does all this has truly been modest before Allah.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #20 — narrated by Ibn Masud (Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"20"},"sequenceIndex":19},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-21","text":"Say: I believe in Allah, and then be steadfast.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #21 — narrated by Sufyan ibn Abdullah (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"21"},"sequenceIndex":20},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-22","text":"I think that most of the people in the Fire are those who died as infants, before they could commit sins.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #22 — narrated by Abu Said al-Khudri (Bukhari)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"22"},"sequenceIndex":21},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-23","text":"Purity is half of faith. Alhamdulillah fills the scales. Subhanallah and Alhamdulillah fill what is between the heaven and the earth. Prayer is a light. Charity is a proof. Patience is illumination. The Quran is a proof for you or against you. Every person sets out in the morning selling his soul, setting it free or destroying it.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #23 — narrated by Abu Malik al-Ashari (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"23"},"sequenceIndex":22},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-24","text":"O people, Allah is pure and He accepts only what is pure. Allah has commanded the believers to do that which He commanded the Messengers.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #24 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"24"},"sequenceIndex":23},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-25","text":"Charity given to a poor person is just charity, but charity given to a relative has two rewards: charity and upholding family ties.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #25 — narrated by Salman ibn Amir (Nasai & Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"25"},"sequenceIndex":24},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-26","text":"Every joint of a person must perform a charity each day that the sun rises: to judge justly between two people is a charity; to help a man with his mount, lifting him onto it or hoisting up his belongings onto it is a charity; a good word is a charity; every step you take to prayers is a charity; and removing a harmful thing from the road is a charity.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #26 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"26"},"sequenceIndex":25},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-27","text":"Righteousness is good character, and wrongdoing is what is hidden in your chest and which you dislike people finding out about.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #27 — narrated by Wabisah ibn Mabad (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"27"},"sequenceIndex":26},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-28","text":"I command you to pray, fast, give charity, perform the pilgrimage and to emigrate, and I warn you of five things: do not listen to the people of innovation; do not dispute with your brother; do not abandon your brother; do not accuse your brother; and do not swear by anyone other than Allah.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #28 — narrated by Abu Najih al-Irbad ibn Sariyyah (Abu Dawud & Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"28"},"sequenceIndex":27},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-29","text":"Whoever can guarantee me what is between his jaws and what is between his legs, I can guarantee him Paradise.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #29 — narrated by Sahl ibn Sad (Bukhari)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"29"},"sequenceIndex":28},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-30","text":"Verily, Allah the Exalted says: Whoever has enmity towards a friend of Mine, then I have declared war upon him. My servant does not draw near to Me with anything more beloved to Me than the religious duties I have imposed upon him. My servant continues to draw near to Me with supererogatory works until I love him. When I love him, I become his hearing with which he hears, his seeing with which he sees, his hand with which he strikes, and his foot with which he walks. Were he to ask something of Me, I would surely give it to him; and were he to seek refuge with Me, I would surely grant him refuge.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #30 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Bukhari)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"30"},"sequenceIndex":29},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-31","text":"Do not envy one another; do not artificially inflate prices against one another; do not hate one another; do not turn away from one another; and do not undercut one another in trade. Be, O servants of Allah, brothers. A Muslim is the brother of a Muslim. He does not oppress him, nor does he fail him, nor does he lie to him, nor does he hold him in contempt.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #31 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"31"},"sequenceIndex":30},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-32","text":"There should be neither harming nor reciprocating harm.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #32 — narrated by Ibn Abbas & Ubadah ibn al-Samit (Ibn Majah & Malik)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"32"},"sequenceIndex":31},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-33","text":"If you were to rely upon Allah with the reliance He is due, He would provide for you just as He provides for the birds: they go out in the morning hungry and come back in the evening full.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #33 — narrated by Umar ibn al-Khattab (Tirmidhi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"33"},"sequenceIndex":32},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-34","text":"Whoever sees a wrong and is able to change it with his hand, let him change it with his hand. If he is not able, then with his tongue; and if he is not able, then with his heart — and this is the weakest form of faith.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #34 — narrated by Abu Said al-Khudri (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"34"},"sequenceIndex":33},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-35","text":"Do not be envious of one another, do not artificially inflate prices, do not hate one another, do not turn away from one another and do not undercut one another. Be, O servants of Allah, brothers.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #35 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"35"},"sequenceIndex":34},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-36","text":"Whoever relieves a believer's distress of the distressful aspects of this world, Allah will rescue him from a difficulty of the difficulties of the Hereafter. Whoever alleviates the lot of a needy person, Allah will alleviate his lot in this world and the next. Whoever shields a Muslim, Allah will shield him in this world and the next. Allah will aid a servant so long as that servant aids his brother. Whoever follows a path to seek knowledge thereby, Allah will make easy for him a path to Paradise. No people gather together in a house of the houses of Allah, reciting the Book of Allah and studying it among themselves, but tranquillity descends upon them, mercy covers them, the angels surround them, and Allah makes mention of them to those in His presence.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #36 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"36"},"sequenceIndex":35},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-37","text":"Verily, Allah has recorded the good deeds and the bad deeds. Then he clarified that: Whoever intended to perform a good deed but did not do it, Allah records it with Himself as a complete good deed. If he intended to do it and did it, Allah records it with Himself as ten good deeds, up to seven hundred times, up to many times over. If he intended to perform an evil deed but did not do it, Allah records it with Himself as a complete good deed. If he intended it and did it, Allah records it as one bad deed.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #37 — narrated by Ibn Abbas (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"37"},"sequenceIndex":36},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-38","text":"Allah the Exalted has said: Whoever draws closer to Me by a hand span, I draw closer to him by an arm's length. Whoever draws closer to Me by an arm's length, I draw closer to him by a fathom. Whoever comes to Me walking, I come to him running.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #38 — narrated by Abu Hurayrah (Bukhari)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"38"},"sequenceIndex":37},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-39","text":"Allah has forgiven my nation for mistakes, forgetfulness, and what they are forced to do.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #39 — narrated by Ibn Abbas (Ibn Majah & al-Bayhaqi)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"39"},"sequenceIndex":38},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-40","text":"Be in this world as though you were a stranger or a wayfarer.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #40 — narrated by Ibn Umar (Bukhari)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"40"},"sequenceIndex":39},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-41","text":"Not one of you will believe until his desire follows what I have brought.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #41 — narrated by Abdullah ibn Amr ibn al-As (an-Nawawi's Arbaeen)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"41"},"sequenceIndex":40},{"id":"hadith-nawawi-42","text":"Allah will not show mercy to one who does not show mercy to people.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"40 Hadith An-Nawawi #42 — narrated by Abdullah ibn Amr ibn al-As (Bukhari & Muslim)","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:nawawi40"],"groups":{"hadith":"42"},"sequenceIndex":41}]}